                            <comment id="13128529" author="kannanm" created="Sun, 16 Oct 2011 22:19:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Now that we have lazy seeks, i.e. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4465&quot; title=&quot;Lazy-seek optimization for StoreFile scanners&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4465&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4465&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we should be able to revert the work/optimization done &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3082&quot; title=&quot;For ICV gets, first look in MemStore before reading StoreFiles&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3082&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3082&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and avoid this bug. What do you folks think?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13128530" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sun, 16 Oct 2011 22:26:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the proposal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13128564" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 01:42:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree. I think delete handling is generally a bit &quot;funky&quot; in HBase (see also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4536&quot; title=&quot;Allow CF to retain deleted rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4536&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4536&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13250447" author="tsuna" created="Tue, 10 Apr 2012 04:00:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems like a pretty bad bug that causes data corruption.  I ran into it this weekend.  Which release do you guys think will have a fix for this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
