                            <comment id="13250968" author="lhofhansl" created="Tue, 10 Apr 2012 19:10:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For 0.96, though.&lt;br/&gt;
I can take this. Can&apos;t promise to work on it today, though.&lt;br/&gt;
Had checked out the code a while ago to make ICV correct w.r.t. to WAL updates, this involves mostly removing some crufty code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252049" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 11 Apr 2012 23:42:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch. Quite trivial, just removing some code and using the existing get without invoking coprocessors&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BUT... To test the performance I jacked up the number of increments per thread in TestAtomicOperation.testIncrementMultiThreads to 10000 and ran it with and without this change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On my machine I find that the test runs around 23-24s with the existing code and around 27-28s with this patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not sure that is a hit we want take.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252050" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 11 Apr 2012 23:44:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also verified that the test included in the patch fails without the other changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
